        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 2:26AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 225 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Briscoe, or 14 miles south of Canadian, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Hemphill
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
